-- Romania to Accept Dollar Bonds as Collateral Starting March 1
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-02-29T12:08:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/romania-to-accept-dollar-bonds-as-collateral-starting-march-1.html
Romania ’s central bank said it will
accept dollar-denominated bonds sold by Romania on international
markets this year as collateral in open-market and monetary
policy operations starting March 1.  The  Banca Nationala a Romaniei  will accept $2.25 billion in
dollar-denominated bonds sold on Jan. 31 and Feb. 28, the
Bucharest-based bank said today in an e-mailed statement.  “The haircut level, the margin deducted from the market
value of eligible assets to obtain the adjusted value thereof,
applicable to the above mentioned securities will be 9 percent
for central bank operations with maximum one month maturity,”
the bank said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
